{"timestamp": "2025-12-06 12:47:30.373357", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\n\nExecutive summary\n- Network health: Critical outage. All host-to-host connectivity in the 10.0.0.0/24 data plane is down.\n- Primary anomaly: All Open vSwitch (OVS) devices are in fail_mode=secure with zero OpenFlow entries and are disconnected from the SDN controller due to “Connection refused.” As a result, no L2/L3 forwarding occurs (including ARP), causing complete blackholing of host traffic.\n\nKey observations and evidence\n1) End-to-end reachability\n- All pings between hosts fail with “Destination Host Unreachable” and 100% packet loss, even for hosts on the same leaf switch:\n  - host_1_1 -> host_1_2: 100% loss, “From 10.0.0.1 Destination Host Unreachable”\n  - host_2_1 -> host_2_2: 100% loss, “From 10.0.0.3 Destination Host Unreachable”\n  - Cross-leaf pairs also fail similarly.\n- This pattern indicates ARP resolution failure (no ARP reply), i.e., no L2 flooding/forwarding by the switches.\n\n2) Host interface configuration (all normal)\n- Each host has the correct /24 IP on eth0 and link state UP/LOWER_UP; only TX counters increment (no RX), consistent with unanswered ARP.\n  - Example: host_1_1 eth0 10.0.0.1/24; route 10.0.0.0/24 via eth0.\n\n3) Switch control-plane state (abnormal)\n- All switches (leaf_1, leaf_2, spine_1) are configured with:\n  - Controller: tcp:20.0.0.100:6633\n  - fail_mode: secure\n  - No OpenFlow entries:\n    - ovs-ofctl dump-flows on all: empty replies.\n  - Controller connection status:\n    - “is_connected: false” and status: {last_error=\"Connection refused\", state=BACKOFF}\n- Management connectivity to the controller host is OK:\n  - leaf_1, leaf_2, spine_1 can ping 20.0.0.100 successfully over 20.0.0.0/24.\n  - Each switch has a management IP on a non-OVS interface (e.g., leaf_1 eth3: 20.0.0.2/24).\n\nInterpretation and fault localization\n- The data plane is not forwarding at all due to lack of OpenFlow rules and fail_mode=secure (which blocks traffic when no controller is available).\n- Since all switches simultaneously report “Connection refused” to tcp:20.0.0.100:6633 while basic IP reachability to 20.0.0.100 is working, the issue is centralized at the controller endpoint rather than the transport network.\n- Therefore, the faulty component is the SDN controller service/listener at 20.0.0.100:6633 (or the configuration of the switches pointing to a non-listening/incorrect port).\n\nRoot cause\n- The SDN controller at 20.0.0.100 is not accepting OpenFlow connections on TCP port 6633 (connection actively refused). With OVS fail_mode=secure and no controller session, the switches have no flow entries and drop all traffic, including ARP. This leads to complete L2/L3 outage across the 10.0.0.0/24 host network.\n\nImpact assessment\n- All host-to-host communication across leaf_1 and leaf_2 is down.\n- Intra-leaf traffic is also impacted because ARP cannot be flooded/resolved without flows.\n- Management plane remains healthy; switches can reach the controller IP at L3 but cannot establish OpenFlow sessions.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 10180, "output_tokens": 2407, "total_tokens": 12587, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 9472}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 1600}}}
